name: ǁʼāū
notes: Nakagawa 2013: 53; check if really general term

name: gúũ-wà-háã
meaning: useless/harmless; non-edible, non-medicinal and non-dangerous plants and animals
notes: a category opposed to the others, Tanaka/Sugawara 2010: 121

name: ǁʰàù
notes: part of the ǀχáa-category (edible vertebrates); Nakagawa 2013: 41; Tanaka/Sugawara 2010: 3, 121

name: kχʼóo-χo
notes: part of the ǀχáa-category (edible vertebrates); Tanaka/Sugawara 2010: 3, 121

name: paa-χò
meaning: dangerous animals, “bite-thing”; synonym: ŋǂīī-ǀùà, ŋǂǐi-ǀoã (carnivores, possible man-killers)
notes: Nakagawa 2013: 81; Tanaka/Sugawara 2010: 16, 121; ŋǂīī-ǀùa: “beast-DIM”, mainly felines and canines, maybe a loan from Naro

name: chõó tcg'au
meaning: vegetable eaten by whites (eg. lettuce, cabbage, spinach)

name: ghòrò kg'oose
meaning: birds of prey (kite, buzzard, falcon, hawk, eagle, harrier, kestrel)
